      <notesStmt>
        <note>Title from colophon. The manuscript's original acquisition label renders the title in Sanskrit as Vāmanākṣarī, under which title Poleman catalogs the ms.</note>
        <note>Written 9-11 lines per leaf.</note>
        <note>Good condition. Mistakes covered over with yellow or written over.</note>
        <note>Begins (f. 1r): śrīkāre jaya kāryāṇīvidyām aiśvaryaṁ eva ca ārogyaṁ kṣemamāmotī labhate nātra saṁśaya (verse 1). akāre śokasaṁtāpaṁ vyavādaṁ saṁgam eva ca avyāhasakalāścaiva arkalābhaśca eva ca (verse 2).</note>
        <note>Ends: jakāre yaśalābhaṁ ca dhaṁna prāmotīmānasāṁ [-]labhate tānna sandeho dhanam aiśvaryam eva ca (verse 51).</note>
        <note>Colophon (f. 4v): ītī śrībāvaṁnākṣarī.</note>
      </notesStmt>
